TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$showHint =3;

$emfSI = random(95,105,1);
$resistance = random(24,36,1);
$resistanceSI = $resistance*10**3;

$currentSI = ($emfSI)/($resistanceSI);
$currentmA = $currentSI*10**3;

Context() -> texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
$PAR

<b>If you do not answer this question correctly in $showHint attempts, you can get a hint.</b>

$PAR
$PAR

What is the sensitivity of the galvanometer (that is, what current gives a full-scale deflection) inside a voltmeter that has a \($resistance\)-<span style="font-family: 'Times'; font-size: 20px";>k&Omega;</span> resistance on its \($emfSI\)-\(\textrm{V}\) scale?

$PAR
$PAR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\textrm{mA}\)

$PAR
$PAR

END_TEXT
BEGIN_HINT
Can you rearrange Ohm's law to solve for current?
END_HINT

Context() -> normalStrings;

ANS(num_cmp("$currentmA"));


